## Reuse a Within Preconditioner

The expensive part of the `within` backend is the preconditioner setup. For
multi-fixed-effect problems, `PyFixest` caches that object during demeaning and
exposes it on `feols` fits as `fit.preconditioner_`.

You can then pass that preconditioner into a later `WithinDemeaner(...)`:

::: {#1ee914d7 .cell execution_count=4}
``` {.python .cell-code}
fit1 = pf.feols(
    fml_y1,
    data=panel,
    demeaner=pf.WithinDemeaner(),
)

fit1.preconditioner_
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=4}
```
WithinPreconditioner(n_obs=2400, n_factors=2, factor_cardinalities=(40, 300), preconditioner_type='additive')
```
:::
:::


::: {#870c2192 .cell execution_count=5}
``` {.python .cell-code}
fit2 = pf.feols(
    fml_y2,
    data=panel,
    demeaner=pf.WithinDemeaner(preconditioner=fit1.preconditioner_),
)

fit2.coef()
```

